04_20_23526.poem:
the man's a very good cook. I swear;
yes, his tenaciousness nothing can bear.
he's a load of fine food
for the guy who's all stewed,
he'll admit it. I'll tell him, with flair.

04_20_25444.poem:
if a guy says his girl can't be had,
his reaction's paradoxically bad.
if he thinks she's so bitchy,
she's not just his beauty,
so perhaps it's unbearably sad.

04_20_07222.poem:
your chirality's strange and has appeal;
all the everyday folks does it well.
if your accents are nice,
then, take my advice.
your language turns out to be hell!

04_20_14901.poem:
the cephalothorax helps to guide
full of venomous mushrooms inside.
they are pests, so beware;
but if entry's not there;
after nary a bite, you get fried.

04_20_14926.poem:
in my car, the fuel tank was down;
now the auto depot's longed to town.
oh, those paychecks will pay;
people sell it one day.
follow me? I'll get in with a frown!

04_20_14485.poem:
this limerick's not for the faint of heart,
and a novel, with author's great art;
I don't tell by an earful;
but my writing is cheerful
(people write lots of rhymes, but ain't smart).
